<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8"/>
    <meta name="description" content="Start collecting plugin analytics with bStats.">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"/>
    <title>bStats — Getting Started</title>

    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="/stylesheets/tailwind.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"/>
    <link href="/stylesheets/style.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"/>
</head>
<body class="bg-slate-950 text-slate-100 antialiased">

<% include ../templates/navigation.ejs %>

<main>
    <section class="relative isolate overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-950 via-slate-900 to-slate-950"></div>
        <div class="absolute inset-x-0 top-[-18rem] -z-20 flex justify-center opacity-70 blur-3xl">
            <div class="h-[28rem] w-[60rem] max-w-full" style="background: radial-gradient(circle at top, var(--accent-color) 0%, rgba(15,118,110,0) 65%);"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-24 sm:py-28 lg:py-32">
            <div class="space-y-6 text-center">
                <span class="accent-pill inline-flex text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em]">Documentation</span>
                <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-5xl">Getting started with bStats</h1>
                <p class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-lg leading-7 text-slate-300">Collect anonymous adoption metrics for your Bukkit, Spigot, BungeeCord, Sponge or Velocity plugin in a few minutes. Follow these steps to add bStats, register your plugin and start publishing dashboards.</p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-4">
                    <a href="/getting-started/include-metrics" class="accent-bg inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full px-5 py-2 text-sm font-semibold shadow-lg shadow-slate-950/50 transition hover:shadow-xl">
                        Include metrics
                    </a>
                    <% if (loggedIn) { %>
                    <a href="/add-plugin" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-white/15 px-5 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white/80 transition hover:border-white/35 hover:text-white">
                        Register my plugin
                    </a>
                    <% } else { %>
                    <a href="/register" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-white/15 px-5 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white/80 transition hover:border-white/35 hover:text-white">
                        Create account
                    </a>
                    <% } %>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-20 grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-2">
                <article class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 p-8 shadow-xl shadow-slate-950/30 backdrop-blur">
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">What bStats collects</h2>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">bStats gathers anonymous runtime information to help you understand your audience: server counts, player totals, Minecraft/Java versions, online mode and optional custom charts defined by you. IP addresses are only used for rate limiting and never linked to chart data.</p>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">Every metric is public. Browse your pluginʼs page—or any other plugin page—to see how the data is visualised.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 p-8 shadow-xl shadow-slate-950/30 backdrop-blur">
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Why it matters</h2>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">Plugin authors use bStats to spot version adoption, plan releases and demonstrate impact to their communities. The metrics dashboard updates a few times per hour and can be embedded, exported or queried via the REST API.</p>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">Keeping bStats enabled is a low-cost way to support the developers whose plugins you rely on.</p>
                </article>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-16 rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/60 p-8 shadow-xl shadow-slate-950/30 backdrop-blur">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Integration checklist</h2>
                <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
                    <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-slate-300">
                        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                            <span class="accent-bg mt-0.5 inline-flex h-7 w-7 flex-none items-center justify-center rounded-full text-xs font-semibold">1</span>
                            <span>Add the bStats dependency. Choose between Maven shading or copying the single Metrics class. The <a href="/getting-started/include-metrics" class="accent-text hover:opacity-80">Include Metrics</a> guide walks you through both.</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                            <span class="accent-bg mt-0.5 inline-flex h-7 w-7 flex-none items-center justify-center rounded-full text-xs font-semibold">2</span>
                            <span>Create an account on bStats (or sign in) and register your plugin. You will get a unique plugin ID used by the metrics constructor.</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-slate-300">
                        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                            <span class="accent-bg mt-0.5 inline-flex h-7 w-7 flex-none items-center justify-center rounded-full text-xs font-semibold">3</span>
                            <span>Instantiate bStats inside your pluginʼs enable/startup routine and optionally add custom charts to highlight extra data.</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                            <span class="accent-bg mt-0.5 inline-flex h-7 w-7 flex-none items-center justify-center rounded-full text-xs font-semibold">4</span>
                            <span>Ship your update. Metrics will start flowing within a few minutes and dashboards will update automatically.</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-16 grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-3">
                <section class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 p-6 shadow-xl shadow-slate-950/30 backdrop-blur">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Custom charts</h3>
                    <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">Highlight unique insights with pie, bar, line or drilldown charts. Configure them in the dashboard or via the REST API.</p>
                    <a href="/help/custom-charts" class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white/80 transition hover:text-white">
                        Explore chart types
                        <svg class="h-4 w-4" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.6" d="M7 5l6 5-6 5"></path>
                        </svg>
                    </a>
                </section>
                <section class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 p-6 shadow-xl shadow-slate-950/30 backdrop-blur">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">REST API</h3>
                    <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">Programmatically fetch plugin stats, compare versions or power external dashboards with the public REST API.</p>
                    <a href="/help/rest-api" class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white/80 transition hover:text-white">
                        Read the reference
                        <svg class="h-4 w-4" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.6" d="M7 5l6 5-6 5"></path>
                        </svg>
                    </a>
                </section>
                <section class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 p-6 shadow-xl shadow-slate-950/30 backdrop-blur">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Disable bStats?</h3>
                    <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">Server owners can opt out by toggling `enabled: false` inside `<code class="rounded bg-slate-900/60 px-1 py-0.5 text-xs">/plugins/bStats/config.yml</code>`. We encourage leaving metrics on to support your favourite plugins.</p>
                    <p class="mt-3 text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">Impact is minimal: data is batched, asynchronous and anonymised.</p>
                </section>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</main>

<% include ../templates/footer.ejs %>
<% include ../templates/globalScripts.ejs %>

</body>
</html>
